        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 24 at 5:46PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 545 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Clio, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Flushing, Frankenmuth, Vassar, Clio, Birch Run, Millington, Mount
Morris, Montrose, Otisville, Otter Lake, Beecher, Tuscola, Burt, and
Thetford Township.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
